<refnamediv><refname>imorientation</refname><refpurpose>Estimate the principal image orientation.</refpurpose></refnamediv>
<refsynopsisdiv><title>Syntax</title><synopsis>angle = imorientation(image)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv><refsection><title>Parameters</title><variablelist><varlistentry><term>image</term><listitem><para>Binary or numeric 2-D image.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>angle</term><listitem><para>Dominant foreground orientation angle in degrees.</para></listitem></varlistentry></variablelist></refsection>
<refsection><title>Description</title><para>Returns the principal second-moment orientation in degrees, measured using the image row and column coordinate convention.</para></refsection>
<refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting><![CDATA[
image = imread(fullpath(getIPCVpath() + "/images/opencv_left01.jpg"));
image = imresize(rgb2gray(image), [120 160]);
angle = imorientation(image);
disp(angle);
imshow(image);
]]></programlisting></refsection>
